const faqs = [
  {
    question: "When does the missed call text send?",
    answer: "Within seconds of the unanswered call ending — before the main contractor searches for the next BCSA member. During full-day erection shifts where your phone sits in the crane cab or the site office from dawn until pack-up, this automatic text keeps your fabrication business commercially visible without interrupting any lift."
  },
  {
    question: "What does the text message say?",
    answer: "The wording is entirely yours — drafted during setup and editable at any time. An effective steelwork message reads: 'Thank you for calling [company name]. We are currently on a steel erection site. We will return your call at the earliest opportunity. Reply with your steelwork requirements for a faster response.' This conveys active on-site capability and technical credibility."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this replace AI Phone Answering?",
    answer: "They function as complementary safeguards. Phone Answering conducts detailed conversations — identifying the frame type, span, eaves height, tonnage, execution class, and programme timing. Missed Call Text Back covers rare bypass scenarios — a call during a critical crane lift when the system is busy, a mobile signal fading inside a steel structural frame, or a caller disconnecting before the AI picks up. Both running simultaneously means no steel enquiry vanishes permanently."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does Missed Call Text Back cost?",
    answer: `This add-on is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month. Structural steel projects span from £800 RSJ installations to £200,000 commercial frame contracts. Recovering one missed call from a developer — who needed a 120-tonne portal frame warehouse confirmed for their programme — through a timely branded text delivers a return that dwarfs the channel cost for years.`
